<dl id="n36149a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36149a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36149a"> 149(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> position precarious</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A consideration of this statement of income and expenditure, and of the number of people who are living under the conditions which it indicates, remind us <mark>how precarious</mark> are the lives of the poor, who are at all times liable to be plunged into poverty by the death or illness of the chief wage-earner. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 157</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c09086h" href="c09all.htm#c09086h">VI.C.09:086(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
